                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar <lb n="2"/>divi <expan><abbr>Traian</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>Parth</abbr><ex>ici</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> divi <lb n="4"/>Nervae <expan><abbr>nep</abbr><ex>os</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Traian</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Hadri</abbr><ex>anus</ex></expan> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>ma</abbr><ex>ximus</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> XIII <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>onsul</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/>III <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> a <expan><abbr>Sumel</abbr><ex>ocenna</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/><expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>assuum</ex></expan> XXVIIII
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Z. 5 (Anfang): wohl TR-Ligatur, die auf der Zeichnung in CIL XVII allerdings nicht erkennbar ist. Die Worte an den Zeilenenden sind entweder abgekürzt oder nicht vollständig erhalten. (B): Mettler: Z. 5: [T]raian(us); Mettler; Sixt; AE 1900; CIL 13, 09084; Haug - Sixt: Z. 9: [m(ilia)].</p>
            </div>
